---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { parish } from '../../parish.config';
---

<BaseLayout title="Visit Us" description="Planning your first visit to a Byzantine Catholic parish? Here's everything you need to know.">
  <section class="page-header page-header--icon">
    <div class="container content-width text-center">
      <h1>Your First Visit</h1>
      <p class="page-header__subtitle">
        You don't need to know anything. You don't need to be ready. 
        You just need to show up. Here's what to expect.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container content-width">

      <!-- Icon Feature -->
      <div class="visit-icon-feature">
        <img src="/images/pantocrator.jpg" alt="Christ Pantocrator, 6th century icon from Saint Catherine's Monastery, Sinai" />
        <p class="visit-icon-caption">Christ Pantocrator ГўпёҺВҖВ” 6th century, Saint Catherine's Monastery, Sinai</p>
      </div>

      <!-- What to Expect -->
      <h2>What You'll Experience</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

      <div class="visit-block">
        <h3>рҹ•ҜпёҸ When You Walk In</h3>
        <p>
          The first thing you'll notice is the smell ГўпёҺВҖВ” <strong>incense</strong>, sweet and thick, 
          the same kind Christians have burned since the first century. Then the icons: not 
          paintings on a wall, but faces looking back at you. Saints. The Theotokos (the Virgin 
          Mary). Christ himself. They've been praying here longer than you've been alive.
        </p>
        <p>
          Ahead of you is the <strong>iconostasis</strong> ГўпёҺВҖВ” a wall of icons separating the 
          nave from the altar. Behind those doors, the Eucharist is prepared. Everything in this 
          room is arranged to say one thing: <em>you have stepped out of the ordinary world.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="visit-block">
        <h3>рҹҺө The Service</h3>
        <p>
          There's no worship band. No screens. The <strong>Divine Liturgy</strong> is almost 
          entirely <strong>sung or chanted</strong> ГўпёҺВҖВ” the prayers themselves are the music, and 
          they've been the same prayers since the 4th century. It's disorienting at first. Then 
          it's beautiful. Then you realize this is how Christians have always worshipped.
        </p>
        <p>
          At Dormition, services are in <strong>English and Ukrainian</strong>. You won't understand 
          every word ГўпёҺВҖВ” that's okay. The Liturgy works on you whether you follow along or not. It 
          lasts about <strong>60ГўпёҺВҖВ“75 minutes</strong>. We mostly stand (ancient Christian practice), 
          but sit whenever you need to. Nobody will judge you.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="visit-block">
        <h3>рҹҚһ Holy Communion</h3>
        <p>
          In the Byzantine tradition, the Body and Blood of Christ are received together on a 
          <strong>small spoon</strong>. When you approach:
        </p>
        <ul class="visit-list">
          <li><strong>Remain standing</strong> (we don't kneel at the altar rail)</li>
          <li><strong>Open your mouth</strong> and tilt your head back slightly</li>
          <li><strong>Do not extend your tongue</strong> ГўпёҺВҖВ” the priest places the spoon gently</li>
          <li><strong>Do not say "Amen"</strong> ГўпёҺВҖВ” the priest speaks the words</li>
          <li>After receiving, take a piece of blessed bread (<em>antidoron</em>) from the tray nearby</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="visit-callout">
          <strong>Who may receive?</strong> All Catholics in good standing with the Church may receive 
          Holy Communion at a Byzantine Catholic Liturgy. If you are not Catholic or not in a state of 
          grace, you are welcome to approach for a blessing ГўпёҺВҖВ” simply cross your arms over your chest.
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="cross-ornament">ГўпёҺВңпёҺВ пёҺ ГўпёҺВңпёҺВ пёҺ ГўпёҺВңпёҺВ пёҺ</div>

      <!-- Common Questions -->
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">I'm a Roman Catholic. Can I attend and receive Communion here?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Absolutely yes. Byzantine Catholics are in full communion with the Pope and the Roman 
          Catholic Church. Attending Divine Liturgy fulfills your Sunday obligation, and you are 
          welcome to receive Holy Communion. The only difference is the rite ГўпёҺВҖВ” the faith is the same.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">I'm Orthodox. What's the difference?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          We share the same liturgical tradition, the same theology of icons, the same ancient 
          prayers. The primary difference is that Byzantine Catholics are in union with the Bishop 
          of Rome (the Pope). You will feel very much at home in our worship. Regarding communion, 
          please speak with the priest.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">I'm not Christian / just curious. Am I welcome?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Very much so. You are welcome to attend any service. There is no pressure to participate 
          in anything that makes you uncomfortable. Simply observe, listen, and take in the beauty. 
          If you'd like to learn more afterward, the priest and parishioners are happy to talk.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">What should I wear?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Come as you are. There is no dress code. You'll see some parishioners in suits and 
          others in casual clothes. What matters is that you're here.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">What language are the services in?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          At Dormition, the 9:00 AM Liturgy is in both <strong>English and Ukrainian</strong>. 
          The 11:30 AM Liturgy is primarily in <strong>Ukrainian</strong>. You do not need to 
          speak Ukrainian to attend ГўпёҺВҖВ” the rhythm and beauty of the Liturgy transcends language.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">Do I need to fast before Communion?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          The Church requires a one-hour fast from food and drink (except water and medicine) before 
          receiving Holy Communion. The traditional Eastern practice is to fast from midnight ГўпёҺВҖВ” some 
          parishioners observe this, but the one-hour rule is sufficient.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <p class="faq-item__question">Can I bring my children?</p>
        <p class="faq-item__answer">
          Please do. In the Byzantine tradition, infants receive Holy Communion from the day of their 
          baptism. Children are full participants in the life of the Church, and a little noise is 
          the sound of a living parish. Don't worry about them being "too loud."
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="cross-ornament">ГўпёҺВңпёҺВ пёҺ ГўпёҺВңпёҺВ пёҺ ГўпёҺВңпёҺВ пёҺ</div>

      <!-- Practical -->
      <h2>Practical Details</h2>
      <hr class="gold-divider gold-divider--left" />

      <div class="visit-details">
        <div class="visit-detail">
          <h4>рҹ“Қ Address</h4>
          <p>
            {parish.address.street}<br />
            {parish.address.city}, {parish.address.province} {parish.address.postalCode}<br />
            <a href={parish.address.mapUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener">Get Directions ГўпёҺВҶВ’</a>
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-detail">
          <h4>ГўпёҺВҸВ° Sunday Services</h4>
          {parish.services.liturgy.map(svc => (
            <p><strong>{svc.time}</strong> ГўпёҺВҖВ” {svc.label} ({svc.language})</p>
          ))}
        </div>

        <div class="visit-detail">
          <h4>рҹ•ҜпёҸ Confession</h4>
          <p>
            <strong>{parish.services.confession.times.join(' & ')}</strong><br />
            {parish.services.confession.note}
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="visit-detail">
          <h4>ГўпёҺВҳпёҺВ• Stay for Coffee</h4>
          <p>
            After the Liturgy, please join us for coffee and fellowship in the parish hall. This is 
            the best way to get to know the community. Visitors are especially welcome ГўпёҺВҖВ” introduce 
            yourself, and someone will happily show you around.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center" style="margin-top: var(--space-3xl);">
        <p style="margin: 0 auto var(--space-lg); max-width: 50ch; font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--color-primary);">
          "Come and see." ГўпёҺВҖВ” John 1:46
        </p>
        <a href="/schedule/" class="btn btn--primary">View Full Schedule ГўпёҺВҶВ’</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-dark), var(--color-primary));
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
    padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    color: var(--color-text-inverse);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .page-header__subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: rgba(250, 246, 239, 0.8);
    max-width: 55ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .visit-block {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .visit-block h3 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .visit-list {
    margin: var(--space-md) 0;
    padding-left: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .visit-list li {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .visit-callout {
    background: rgba(201, 168, 76, 0.1);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 0 var(--radius-sm) var(--radius-sm) 0;
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .visit-details {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .visit-detail {
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
  }

  .visit-detail h4 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .visit-detail p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .visit-icon-feature {
    float: right;
    width: 220px;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-xl) var(--space-2xl);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .visit-icon-feature img {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
  }

  .visit-icon-caption {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .visit-icon-feature {
      float: none;
      width: 180px;
      margin: 0 auto var(--space-xl);
    }
  }
</style>
